Package au.edu.anu.twapps.mm.graphEditor

Interface StructureEditor

All Known Implementing Classes:
StructureEditorAdapter
public interface StructureEditor
Interface for the graph structure editor for ModelMaker. All these methods are in the context of a single user-selected node. This node, represented by NodeEditor is assumed available in implementations of this interface.
Author:
Ian Davies - 11 Jan. 2019

  • Method Details

    • filterChildSpecs

      List<fr.cnrs.iees.omugi.graph.impl.SimpleDataTreeNode> filterChildSpecs​(Iterable<fr.cnrs.iees.omugi.graph.impl.SimpleDataTreeNode> childNodeSpecs)
      Filters the list of potential child specifications to just those applicable to the current state of the configuration graph (e.g. specifications for children that have 1..1 multiplicity and already exist are removed from the returned list.
      Parameters:
      childNodeSpecs - List of all potential child specifications.
      Returns:
      List of child specifications relevant to the current state of the configuration graph.

    • filterEdgeSpecs

      List<fr.cnrs.iees.omhtk.utils.Tuple<String,​LayoutNode,​fr.cnrs.iees.omugi.graph.impl.SimpleDataTreeNode>> filterEdgeSpecs​(Iterable<fr.cnrs.iees.omugi.graph.impl.SimpleDataTreeNode> edgeSpecs)
      Filters the list of potential out-edge specifications to just those applicable to the current state of the configuration graph (e.g. specifications for out-edges that have a 1..1 multiplicity and already exist are not included in the result.
      Parameters:
      edgeSpecs - List of all potential out-edge specifications.
      Returns:
      A list (can be empty) of tuples the out-edge label, the end-node and the out-edge specification.

    • getOrphanedChildren

      List<LayoutNode> getOrphanedChildren​(Iterable<fr.cnrs.iees.omugi.graph.impl.SimpleDataTreeNode> childSpecs)
      Returns a list of nodes without parents whose specifications appear in the childSpecs list. This situation can arise when editing the configuration graph when a user wants to delete a parent or reassign the parent of a node to a different parent.
      Parameters:
      childSpecs - List of relevant child specifications of the node being edited.
      Returns:
      List of valid child LayoutNodes.

    • onNewChild

      void onNewChild​(String childLabel, String childId, fr.cnrs.iees.omugi.graph.impl.SimpleDataTreeNode childBaseSpec)
      Actions required to construct a new child node.
      Parameters:
      childLabel - The child's label
      childId - A suggested name (can be changed by the user but its uniqueness within the scope of the configuration graph will be enforced.
      childBaseSpec - The specification of the new child node.

      Actions required to construct a new out-edge.
      Parameters:
      details - A tuple contains the edge label, LayoutNode (end-node) to which the edge connects and the edge specifications.
      duration - Duration in ms of animation.

      true if renamed, false otherwise.

    • onDeleteParentLink

      void onDeleteParentLink​(LayoutNode child)
      Remove the relationship between a child and its parent. The tree graph will have more than one root until either the child is deleted or a parent assigned.
      Parameters:
      child - The child whose parent-child relationship to the currently select node is to be removed.

    • onOptionalProperties

      boolean onOptionalProperties​(List<fr.cnrs.iees.omugi.graph.impl.SimpleDataTreeNode> propertySpecs, List<fr.cnrs.iees.omhtk.utils.Duple<LayoutEdge,​fr.cnrs.iees.omugi.graph.impl.SimpleDataTreeNode>> optionalEdgePropertySpecs)
      Actions require to add/remove optional properties from a node or edge.

      optionalEdgePropertySpecs - List of optional property specifications for all out-edges of the currently selected node.
